  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Chheang et al.",
    "recently conducted a study on the use of a virtual assistant with generative AI for anatomy learning in VR.",
    "They revealed that VR along with an embedded virtual assistant (avatar) was more effective at answering questions that needed analysis (deeper comprehension) than a screen-based assistant [107].",
    "The study also provides insights into usability and user experience in VR powered by AI assistants, suggesting this technology has potential for education beyond just anatomy.",
    "This work opens the door for VR instructors equipped with generative AI to transform orthopedic education by potentially improving knowledge retention and preparing future surgeons for complex procedures."
  ],
